      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>gem</strong> <strong>lettuce </strong>then pat it dry with kitchen paper, remove 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12] </span>leaves and set aside then shred the <strong>inner</strong> <strong>core</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>cucumber</strong> into batons and roughly chop the <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>sticky</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and <strong>red</strong> <strong>Thai</strong> <strong>curry</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>shallot</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>,<strong> </strong>the <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>and <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>sticky rice mixture</strong></p>",
